    "content": "Goal\n* Please change \"it's\" to \"its\".\n\n* Please format the mirror map using the multi-line monospace syntax (3 backticks before and after the block of the text), like this:\n```\n(some text)\n(some more text)\n(some more text)\n```\n\n* Please clarify what is meant by an \"invalid digit\".\n\n* Please format \"INVALID\" as a {{constant}}.\n\nOutput\n* Please format \"INVALID\" as a {{constant}}.\n\nConstraints\n* Please update the upper bound.\n\nCases\n* Each test and its validator should cover the *SAME SCENARIO* scenario but with slightly different inputs and outputs (except for the INVALID cases). Please revise the cases accordingly. For example,\n  • Pair 1 is simple.\n  • One of the middle pairs cover [[s]] with a few leading 0s.\n  • The second last pair contains long \"invalid\" cases.\n  • The last pair contains long \"valid\" cases.\n  (These are just examples and you should need more than 4 pairs of cases in total.)\n\nThanks.",
